<Link id="l01256" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1256"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// A mangled (non-wide) string literal stores the total length of the string it</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01257" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1257"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// refers to (passed in NumBytes), and it contains up to 32 bytes of actual text</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01258" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1258"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// (passed in StringBytes, NumChars).</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01259" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1259" lineLink="#ae0053b0368c4b20d378ba4db4edf9586"><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">static</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">unsigned</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="#ae0053b0368c4b20d378ba4db4edf9586">guessCharByteSize</a>(</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">const</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> uint8&#95;t &#42;StringBytes, </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">unsigned</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> NumChars,</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01262" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1262"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01263" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1263"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// If the number of bytes is odd, this is guaranteed to be a char string.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01264" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1264"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (NumBytes % 2 == 1)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01265" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1265"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">return</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> 1;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01266" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1266"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01267" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1267"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// All strings can encode at most 32 bytes of data.  If it&#39;s less than that,</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01278" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1278"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01279" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1279"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// The whole string was not able to be encoded.  Try to look at embedded null</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01280" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1280"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// terminators to guess.  The heuristic is that we count all embedded null</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01281" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1281"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// terminators.  If more than 2/3 are null, it&#39;s a char32.  If more than 1/3</span></CodeLine>
